comment_data.body:
If I remember correctly, the class is needed because an instance is default-constructed by value on the internal closure class.

(There's a separate debate here about whether to capture C++ references by value or reference in the closure of course, but I've gone for value as the safe option).

Either way, with this choice the captured iterator does need to be default constructable to compile.

Your change is a good idea but it hides the base class constructor. I'll propose a different change that should fix it

```suggestion
class DoublePointerIterDefaultConstructible: public DoublePointerIter {
    // an alternate version that is default-constructible
public:
    DoublePointerIterDefaultConstructible() {}
    DoublePointerIterDefaultConstructible(double* start, int len) :
        DoublePointerIter(start, len)
    {}
    
};
```

